				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm pretty certain that the RF demodulation step will limit it hard to 4.2MHz, even though the NES (and probably the SNES?) generates content above there.<br /><br />Visually, the maximum horizontal spatial frequency out of the NES is f_pixel/2, or ~2.7MHz; a very sharp lowpass filter at 4.2MHz should remove all of its (all odd) overtones, so spatially I believe it would appear as a sine wave before the gamma correction of the TV.<br /><br />I'm not certain how visible that will be; with old CRT sets you'll probably run into the finite dimensions of the cathode ray itself. On an LCD TV the effect will probably be slightly more visible.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

